

h3	count

pre
	<number> = <b>count</b> <text>
	<number> = <b>count</b> <list>

	<number> = <b>count</b> ( <text> )
	<number> = <b>count</b> ( <list> )

p
	Querry the number of elements in a text or in a list.
p
	Returns a numeric value.
p
	You can also count the number of entries in a directory or the length of a file. But this effectively works, because the function <tt>dir</tt> returens a list and function <tt>file</tt> returns a text value. (Version 0.8.7) This will be improved.

+ ../../includes/functions with 1 arg.txt

p
	e.g.:
shell
	i> count globals  o>  0
	i> count{1,2,3,4,5}  o> 5
	i> count "12345"  o> 5
	i> count env  o> 40
	i> count dir "."  o> 26
	i> <>



